				 Direct tax collections up 43%
 OUR CORRESPONDENT 																								New Delhi, Nov. 19: Aided by buoyant economic growth and improved compliance, the Centres direct tax collections grew 42.9 per cent to Rs 1,40,373 crore till November 15 from Rs 98,216 crore a year ago.																								With this, net direct tax collections till November 15 stood at 52 per cent of the budgeted target of Rs 2,67,490 crore for this fiscal, said a finance ministry statement.																								In February, the government had set a direct tax target of Rs 2,67,000 crore for 2007-08. 																								Corporate tax registered a growth of 45.74 per cent at Rs 83,934 crore against Rs 57,593 crore a year ago, while personal income tax, including fringe benefit tax, securities transaction tax and banking cash transaction tax, grew 39.96 per cent to Rs 56,212 crore compared with Rs 40,453 crore. 
